  <description type="morphology">Stems erect to ascending or decumbent; herbage hirtellous or villoso-pilose or densely gray-tomentose (hairs flattened, vitreous, long) to glabrate, sometimes stipitate-glandular. Leaf blades linear to oblanceolate or spatulate-oblong, 10–40 × 2–6(–9) mm, not thick-fleshy, margins of at least the proximal pinnately lobed or shallowly toothed. Heads in corymbiform arrays. Corollas 5–7 mm. Cypselae 2.3–3.6 mm. 2n = 24.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Flowering (Apr–)Jul–Dec.</description>
  <description type="habitat">Coastal bluffs and dunes, sandy flats, salt marsh borders, occasionally on dry slopes;</description>
  <description type="elevation">5–400 m;</description>
  <description type="distribution">Calif.; Mexico (Baja California).</description>
